issue.title: Error building the java wrapper

labels.name: bug
labels.description: A bug in behaviour or functionality

issue.body:
# Build Failed
When generating the Java wrapper file from the web3j command terminal, the build is failed with incompatile types.


## Steps To Reproduce
I exported the json abi from the following url:
[Url](https://api.ftmscan.com/api?module=contract&action=getabi&address=0x261ABeFd8E8895d9E68421888e7bDF8042E6A96F)
and added it in my project
Generated the wrapper by using the following command:
web3j generate solidity -a path_to_json_file -o /my_project_path/app/src/main/java -p package_name
The file generated successfully but  the build failed with incompatible types

### Expected behavior
Successful file generation
Successful build of the application
Ability to access the contract functions

### Actual behavior
App build fails


## Environment

- Web3j version :1.4.2
- Java version: openJdk 16.0.2
- Operating System : Mac M1


## Additional context
Logs:
`'staticExtractEventParametersWithLog(org.web3j.abi.datatypes.Event, org.web3j.protocol.core.methods.response.Log)' in 'org.web3j.tx.Contract' cannot be applied to '(org.web3j.abi.datatypes.Event, org.web3j.protocol.core.methods.response.TransactionReceipt)'`

- [fantomscan](https://api.ftmscan.com/api?module=contract&action=getabi&address=0x261ABeFd8E8895d9E68421888e7bDF8042E6A96F) references

pull_request.title: Fix dynamic array decode null pointer
pull_request.body:
### What does this PR do?
fix decodeDynamicStructElements NPE
lower version codegen does not generate @parameterized annotation when use DynamicArray parameter, which will cause the error as below that confuse people
![image](https://github.com/web3j/web3j/assets/18752800/04c0881e-1312-4253-8873-f3d5a2227e6e)


### Where should the reviewer start?
use the test case: org.web3j.abi.FunctionReturnDecoderTest#testDecodeDynamicStruct3
remove the Annotation can see the case
![image](https://github.com/web3j/web3j/assets/18752800/5f91bbd3-23a8-49ca-9d04-501f0bf77bf8)

### Why is it needed?
https://github.com/web3j/web3j/issues/1726#issuecomment-1605250651
